TAKE of Burgundy-Pitch, Roſin,
and Bees-wax, of each one ounce;
melt theſe together: Then take three-
quarters of an ounce of coarſe Turpen-
tine, and half an ounce of Oyl of Mace;
melt theſe with the other, and keep it
for Uſe: When you have Occaſion,
ſpread it on Sheep's-leather prick'd full
of Holes; and when you lay it on,
grate ſome Nutmeg over it.
